Usage: reportMultibit [-help] [-bit <bit>] [-outFile <file name>]
                      [-type {comb latch flop seq iso ls}] [-cell <cell name> | -library  | -reasonNotMerged <unmerged reason> | -notMergedSummary  | -equiv ] [-hinst <hinst> | -library  | -cell <cell name> | -equiv ]

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-bit <bit>                             # Specify bit of multiBit iso/ls
                                       # (int, optional)
-cell <cell name>                      # Reports the cell details and
                                       # equivalence information of a single
                                       # lib-cell (string, optional)
-equiv                                 # Reports equivalnce summary of
                                       # lib-cells of selected type
                                       # (bool, optional)
-hinst <hinst>                         # Hinst on which reporting is to be done
                                       # (string, optional)
-library                               # Reports flipflop/latch equivalence
                                       # (bool, optional)
-notMergedSummary                      # Reports summary of not merged
                                       # instances (bool, optional)
-outFile <file name>                   # Output file name (string, optional)
-reasonNotMerged {All Area BankLabelPartition BankLabelRegister Bus CellEquivalent ClockPinDangling Connection Constraint ControlTerm DRV Distance Legalization Location MisMatch Partition Power SafetyPartition SafetySerCell ScanConnection SePinDangling Timing Unknown UnmatchedPins User}
                                       # Reports the instances that could not
                                       # be merged for specified reason
                                       # (enum, optional)
-type {comb latch flop seq iso ls}     # Reports for the given type of cells
                                       # (enum, optional)